This Privacy Policy explains how your data is collected, used, and stored when using the xCloudd Discord Bot ("the Bot"). By using the Bot, you agree to this policy.

1. Information Collected
The Bot may collect and store the following data:

User IDs: To track user activity or assign virtual currency or roles.

Server IDs and names: To identify which servers use the Bot.

Interaction Data: Including command usage, timestamps, and user input relevant to bot features.

Game Data: Such as virtual currency balance, winnings, and game history.

Note: No sensitive personal information (such as email addresses, real names, or payment data) is collected.

2. How We Use Your Data
Data collected by the Bot is used to:

Provide and improve Bot features.

Track user progress (e.g. coins, achievements).

Detect abuse or bugs and improve reliability.

Maintain logs for moderation or analytics purposes.

3. Data Sharing
We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties.

Data may be shared only if required by law or to respond to legal processes (e.g. court orders).

Limited data (such as a user ID) may be visible to server administrators using the Botâ€™s admin tools.

4. Data Retention
Data is retained only for as long as it is necessary for the functionality of the Bot.

You may request the removal of your data by contacting the developer.

5. Your Rights
You have the right to request access to or deletion of your data.

You may stop data collection at any time by removing the Bot from your server.

6. Security
Reasonable security measures are taken to protect your data.

However, no system is 100% secure. Use the Bot at your own risk.

7. Contact
